<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-12-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-12-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="451" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d451">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/988.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-12-04">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 4, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Evidence was had today of real success for the Department’s policy when
                            an orderly meeting was held in the plaza with moderate speeches and no
                            interference by the Government; police were substituted for soldiers.
                            Arrests, however, are still being made.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>